    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-06T03:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-06T03:44:00-05:00" n="340"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/638: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-06T08:00:00-00:44"
                            >December 6, 1929—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s circular telegram dated December 1, 4 p.m., complied with yesterday.
                        Barclay<note n="72" xml:id="d340fn72">Edwin Barclay, Liberian Secretary of
                        State.</note> states that Liberia will support Pact of Paris and intend[s]
                    to issue similar statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
